==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Allocation
<hw>Al`lo*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>allocatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>allocation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of putting one thing to another; a placing; disposition;
arrangement.</def> <rj><au>Hallam.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An allotment or apportionment; <as>as, an
<ex>allocation</ex> of shares in a company</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>allocation</qex> of the particular portions of Palestine
to its successive inhabitants.</q> <rj><qau>A. R.
Stanley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The admission of an item in an account, or an
allowance made upon an account; -- a term used in the English
exchequer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Allocatur</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
